PN,30604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1780369438
OL,3,CQuentin Blake Centre for Illustration
OL,4,Cto showcase 'overlooked' art form
OL,6,FAhead of the opening, centre director
OL,7,FLindsey Glen told The Press
OL,8,FAssociation: "In 2002 Quentin Blake
OL,9,Ffirst had the idea of a national
OL,10,Fcentre for illustration.
OL,12,F"He could see that illustration was
OL,13,Fsomething that's in all our lives and
OL,14,Fhas been throughout time, but really
OL,15,Fhas been very much overlooked in
OL,16,Fpublic art spaces.
OL,26,@pD@NOUtD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1780369438
OL,3,CQuentin Blake Centre for Illustration
OL,4,Cto showcase 'overlooked' art form
OL,6,F"So he set about doing something about
OL,7,Fthat, a place with illustration above
OL,8,Fthe door, and finally, almost 25 years
OL,9,Flater, that dream is becoming a
OL,10,Freality."
OL,12,FAfter "outgrowing" a previous space in
OL,13,FKings Cross, Glen said it was clear
OL,14,Fthere was a "huge appetite" for this
OL,15,Fwork.
OL,17,FAfter the space sat derelict for
OL,18,Fdecades, it has now been transformed `
OL,19,Fwith London's oldest surviving
OL,20,Fwindmill to be used as a space for
OL,21,Fresidency programmes.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@IO]tD@GOUtD@RO]vD@MOUvD@[O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1780369438
OL,3,CQuentin Blake Centre for Illustration
OL,4,Cto showcase 'overlooked' art form
OL,6,FSpeaking about the importance of
OL,7,Fshowcasing illustration, Glen said it
OL,8,Fhad "been used throughout time to
OL,9,Fshare stories and ideas, to try and
OL,10,Fpersuade us, to instruct us".
OL,12,F"It's absolutely a fundamental part of
OL,13,Fhuman communication, and yet really,
OL,14,Fthere's been no place, no one place,
OL,15,Fwhere you could come to explore it,
OL,16,Fand now today there is," she said.
OL,18,FSir Quentin had his first illustration
OL,19,Fpublished in Punch magazine in 1949
OL,20,Fwhen he was still at school and he has
OL,21,Fworked on more than 500 books.
OL,26,@pD@EOUrD@\O]tD@AOUxD@XO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1780369438
OL,3,CQuentin Blake Centre for Illustration
OL,4,Cto showcase 'overlooked' art form
OL,6,FWith an almost 80-year career and more
OL,7,Fthan 50,000 pieces in his archives,
OL,8,Fthe centre's artistic director Olivia
OL,9,FAhmad had a huge task deciding what to
OL,10,Fpick for the first exhibition.
OL,12,FExplaining how they settled on
OL,13,FPerformance, she said the illustrator
OL,14,Foften compared his work to that of a
OL,15,Ftheatre director.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1780369438
OL,3,CQuentin Blake Centre for Illustration
OL,4,Cto showcase 'overlooked' art form
OL,6,F"Quentin is an illustrator and draws
OL,7,Fpictures and uses ink and paper but
OL,8,Fneeds to cast the characters, or in
OL,9,Fhis case draw them, design the
OL,10,Fcostumes, sets and then decide what
OL,11,Fthe actions are going to be.
OL,13,F"Thinking about performance is really
OL,14,Ffundamental to the way Quentin thinks
OL,15,Fabout his work," she told PA.
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOUwD@PO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/14
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30609
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1780369438
OL,3,CQuentin Blake Centre for Illustration
OL,4,Cto showcase 'overlooked' art form
OL,6,F"But performers also find their way
OL,7,Finto his work very often ` there's a
OL,8,Flot of harlequins and acrobats and
OL,9,Fclowns. We saw that in his work from
OL,10,Fthe 1950s to now, so we thought that
OL,11,Fwould be a great way to look at many
OL,12,Fdifferent things from his archives."
OL,14,FShe also said visitors would not only
OL,15,Fbe able to see works they "know and
OL,16,Flove", but other pieces that even Sir
OL,17,FQuentin "hasn't seen for a long time".
OL,19,FAfter working with the illustrator for
OL,20,Fover a decade now, Ahmad said drawing
OL,21,Fwas "like breathing for him".
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@dO]wD@[OUxD@EO]yD@IOUyD@eO]}D@
OL,26,AEOU}D@\O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/14
